
Installation notes on pythonFlu

- download managedFlu, confFlu, pythonFlu from 
  http://sourceforge.net/projects/pythonflu/files/9.1-SWIG/

- python 2.7 version
- swig 2.0.6 version (2.0.10 does not work)

-intallation steps

  1. confFlu and managedFlu: build and install (or use precompiled packages)
  2. OpenFoam 2.0.1 version: build and install (or use precompiled packages)
     - use system openmpi (edit etc/bashrc to match this)

  3. pythonFlu package build and installation
     - make env.sh (copy env.sh.example) to match your system
        -add line to the end of env.sh
            export LD_LIBRARY_PATH=$LD_LIBRARY_PATH:/usr/lib64/openmpi/lib
     - source ./env.sh
     - ./build_configure
     - ./configure
     - source ./bashrc
     - make
     - edit  /install-scripts/install_pythonFlu.sh script
           -pythonflu_dir="pythonflu-installation-dir"
           -pythonflu_m4dir="pythonflu-installation-dir"
           where "pythonflu-installation-dir" is not the same directory as the source directory
     - sudo make install
